      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(byteplus): bound video-generation success response reads",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`readBytePlusJsonResponse` in `extensions/byteplus/video-generation-provider.ts` reads both the **submit task** and **poll status** success JSON with an unbounded `await response.json()`. The BytePlus endpoint is untrusted external content; a hostile or misconfigured `baseUrl` can stream an arbitrarily large body on either path with no byte ceiling, buffering the whole payload into memory — a memory-pressure / hang (OOM) vector. The sibling video **buffer download** in the same file was already bounded with `readResponseWithLimit`; this closes the remaining unbounded JSON reads.\n\n## Evidence\n\nReuses the shared bounded reader `readProviderJsonResponse` (16 MiB cap, cancels the stream on overflow) — same pattern as the recently merged #95218 / #96027 / #96038. Plugin-scoped, no new abstraction; the provider-owned `... malformed JSON response` error is preserved.\n\nReal behavior proof (live vitest, not mocked): two real `ReadableStream` overflow tests (submit and poll), each asserting `JSON response exceeds 16777216 bytes` is thrown, the stream is canceled, and the body is not fully pulled.\n\n```\nTests  13 passed (13)\n```\n",
